<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Table of Japanese Kanji radicals</span></h1>
<div id="bodyContent">
<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
<div id="contentSub">  (Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kanji_radical&amp;redirect=no" title="Kanji radical">Kanji radical</a>)</div>
<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
Jump to: <a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, <a href="#p-search">search</a>
</div>
<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><b>Kanji <a href="/wiki/Radical_(Chinese_character)" title="Radical (Chinese character)" class="mw-redirect">radicals</a></b> are a Japanese version of 214 <a href="/wiki/Chinese_characters" title="Chinese characters" class="mw-redirect">Chinese characters</a> called <a href="/wiki/Kangxi_radical" title="Kangxi radical">Kangxi radicals</a>.</p>
<p>The Kangxi dictionary lists a total of 47,035 characters divided among the 214 radicals, the frequency is from that set.</p>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/J%C5%8Dy%C5%8D_kanji" title="Jōyō kanji">Jōyō</a> frequency is from the set of 2,136 <a href="/wiki/J%C5%8Dy%C5%8D_kanji" title="Jōyō kanji">Jōyō</a> kanji.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Top 25% means that this radical makes up 25% of <a href="/wiki/J%C5%8Dy%C5%8D_kanji" title="Jōyō kanji">Jōyō</a> kanji. Top 50% means that this radical plus the Top 25% make up 50% of <a href="/wiki/J%C5%8Dy%C5%8D_kanji" title="Jōyō kanji">Jōyō</a> kanji. Top 75% means that this radical plus the Top 50% make up 75% of <a href="/wiki/J%C5%8Dy%C5%8D_kanji" title="Jōyō kanji">Jōyō</a> kanji.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Many radicals are not commonly written by themselves so most people wouldn't know how their <a href="/wiki/Hiragana" title="Hiragana">Hiragana</a> reading, but where possible the common reading is given instead of the technical reading.</p>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Simplified_table_of_Japanese_kanji_radicals">Simplified table of Japanese kanji radicals</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Table_of_Japanese_Kanji_radicals&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Simplified table of Japanese kanji radicals">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Table_of_Japanese_Kanji_radicals&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Simplified table of Japanese kanji radicals" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>191 essential radicals.</p>
<p>Position category:</p>
<ul>
<li>へん (hen) - left <a href="/wiki/%E2%97%A7" title="◧" class="mw-redirect">◧</a> - radical forms the left component of a kanji.</li>
<li>つくり (tsukuri) - right <a href="/wiki/%E2%97%A8" title="◨" class="mw-redirect">◨</a> - radical forms the right component of a kanji.</li>
<li>かんむり (kanmuri) - top <a href="/wiki/%E2%96%80" title="▀" class="mw-redirect">▀</a> - radical forms the top component of a kanji.</li>
<li>あし (ashi) - bottom <a href="/wiki/%E2%96%84" title="▄" class="mw-redirect">▄</a> - radical forms the bottom component of a kanji.</li>
<li>かまえ (kamae) - wrap <a href="/wiki/%E2%96%A1" title="□" class="mw-redirect">□</a> - radical encloses the other kanji components.</li>
<li>たれ (tare) - top-left <a href="/wiki/%E2%96%9B" title="▛" class="mw-redirect">▛</a> - radical forms the left and top components of a kanji.</li>
<li>にょう (nyou) - bottom-left <a href="/wiki/%E2%96%99" title="▙" class="mw-redirect">▙</a> - radical forms the left and bottom component of a kanji.</li>
</ul>
<p>Because this is a simplified list the reading is only given if the kanji is used on its own.</p>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Examples are taken from the Kangxi radical page and therefore may not be commonly used in Japanese. So far only 匕 and 亡 contain updated examples using <a href="/wiki/J%C5%8Dy%C5%8D_kanji" title="Jōyō kanji">jōyō kanji</a>.</li>
<li>This list is still under construction.</li>
</ul>

<td>口古可名君否呉告周味命和哲唐善器</td>
</tr>
